There are four transport modes in [[en/Manual/OpenTTD|OpenTTD]]: Rail, Road, Sea and Air. Each has its own construction method.


*[[File:it/Railroad build button.png]] '''[[en/Manual/Railway construction]]''' - Build [[en/Manual/Railway station|train stations]], connecting [[en/Manual/Building tracks|railway track]], and [[en/signals]] for [[en/trains]].
*[[File:en/Road build button.png]] '''[[en/Manual/Roadway construction]]''' - Build either [[en/Manual/Loading Bays#Bus Loading Bay|bus stations]] and [[en/Manual/Loading Bays#Lorry Loading Bay|truck stations]], and connect them with roads for [[en/buses]] and [[en/Manual/Road vehicles|trucks]].
*[[File:en/Dock build button.png]] '''[[en/Manual/Waterway construction]]''' - Build [[en/docks]], [[en/waypoints|buoys]], [[en/canals]] for [[en/ships]] to follow.
*[[File:en/Airport build button.png]] '''[[en/Manual/Airport construction]]''' - Build [[en/airports]] and direct [[en/Manual/Aircraft|planes]] between them.

